---
import Layout from "../layouts/layouts.astro";
---

<Layout title="Nardelli" currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}>
	<h1>Welcome</h1>

	<p>
		Welcome to <strong>Nardelli Nespolo</strong>, a homely escape on the Tuscan–Umbrian border. We hope you enjoy everything Umbria and Tuscany have to offer — and that the house makes a perfect base for exploring the area at your own pace.
		We want everyone who stays at Nardelli to have a wonderful experience and to fall in love with this corner of Italy the way we have.<br><br>
		Nardelli was bought by <strong>Billy McCarthy</strong> back in <strong>20XX</strong>, and it became a place that Billy and his partner Des truly cherished. They shared it generously with friends and family, and guests were always welcomed with open arms.
		Billy passed away in <strong>2016</strong>, but the house was left to the wider family to continue enjoying and sharing. We’ve all grown very fond of Nardelli and the surrounding area — and we hope you will too.
	</p>
<p style="margin-top: -6px; color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600;">
	
	Everything you need for a relaxed stay at Nardelli — from house basics to local favourites.
</p>

<p>
	We created this website to help you settle into Nardelli and get acquainted with everything it has to offer.
	It covers the essentials about the house and the local area, along with our recommendations for nearby restaurants, bars and day trips.
	Nardelli is not rental accommodation, but our home away from home — a place we love sharing with family and friends.
	That means it may not always have every polished detail or service you might expect from a holiday rental, but we hope it feels personal, comfortable and full of character.
	And when it’s time to say goodbye, please don’t forget to use the <strong>Leaving Checklist</strong> before you go.
</p>

<section class="heroCard">
	<div class="collage">
		<img class="tile tileHero" src="/photos/House.jpeg" alt="Nardelli" loading="lazy" />
		<img class="tile" src="/photos/Kitchen.jpeg" alt="Kitchen" loading="lazy" />
		<img class="tile tileGardenTable" src="/photos/GardenTable.jpeg" alt="Garden table" loading="lazy" />
		<img class="tile" src="/photos/Bedroom.jpeg" alt="Bedroom" loading="lazy" />
		<img class="tile" src="/photos/Bedroom2.jpeg" alt="Bedroom 2" loading="lazy" />
		<img class="tile tileSpanTwo tilePool" src="/photos/Pool.jpeg" alt="Garden and pool" loading="lazy" />
	</div>
</section>

	<style>

	.heroCard {
	background: var(--card);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	border-radius: var(--radius);
	padding: 16px;
	margin: 12px 0 18px;
}

.collage {
	display: grid;
	gap: 10px;
	grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr 1fr;
	grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 150px);
}

.tilePool {
	object-position: center 60% !important;
}

.tileGardenTable {
	object-position: center 80% !important;
}

.tile {
	width: 100%;
	height: 100%;
	object-fit: cover;
	object-position: center;
	display: block;
	border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
	border: 1px solid var(--border);
	background: var(--bg);
}

/* Main house image on the left */
.tileHero {
	grid-row: 1 / span 3;
	grid-column: 1;
}

/* Pool spans the two smaller columns on the bottom row */
.tileSpanTwo {
	grid-column: 2 / span 2;
}

/* Mobile: stack all images */
@media (max-width: 859px) {
	.collage {
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		grid-template-rows: none;
	}

	.tile,
	.tileHero,
	.tileSpanTwo {
		grid-column: auto;
		grid-row: auto;
		height: 220px;
	}


}

</style>

</Layout>